Default is no parent (empty or -). ## The identity above is used for resolving the reference so it must be specified. # # parent: - # ## Adds a prefix to the identity of cells to make sure they do not collide with existing cells (whose ## IDs are numbers from 0..n, sometimes with a GUID prefix in the context of realtime collaboration). ## Default is csvimport-. # # namespace: csvimport- # ## Connections between rows ("from": source colum, "to": target column). ## Label, style and invert are optional. Defaults are '', current style and false. ## If placeholders are used in the style, they are replaced with data from the source. ## An optional placeholders can be set to target to use data from the target instead. ## In addition to label, an optional fromlabel and tolabel can be used to name the column ## that contains the text for the label in the edges source or target (invert ignored). ## The label is concatenated in the form fromlabel + label + tolabel if all are defined. ## The target column may contain a comma-separated list of values. ## Multiple connect entries are allowed. # # connect: {"from": "manager", "to": "name", "invert": true, "label": "manages", \ # "style": "curved=1;endArrow=blockThin;endFill=1;fontSize=11;"} # connect: {"from": "refs", "to": "id", "style": "curved=1;fontSize=11;"} # ## Node x-coordinate. Default is auto. # # width: auto # ## Node height. Possible value is a number (in px), auto or an @ sign followed by a column ## name that contains the value for the height. targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date_time_date,1s),
  demand AS metric,
  delay,
  loss
FROM flowcharting
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date_time_date)
GROUP BY 1,2
ORDER BY $__timeGroup(date_time_date,1s)

SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date_time_date,1s),
  demand AS metric,
  avg(rate) AS "rate"
FROM linkrate
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date_time_date)
GROUP BY 1,2
ORDER BY $__timeGroup(date_time_date,1s)

SELECT
  srcIP AS "Source(0-99)",
  dstIP AS "Destination(0-99)",
  flow AS "Flow/kB"
FROM traffic
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date_time_date)
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY $__timeGroup(date_time_date,1s)
